1.1.3 Evaluation of chronicity
Practice Point 1.1.3.1: Proof of chronicity (duration of a minimum of 3 months) can be established by:
(i) review of past measurements/estimations of GFR;
(ii) review of past measurements of albuminuria or proteinuria and urine microscopic
examinations;
(iii) imaging ﬁndings such as reduced kidney size and reduction in cortical thickness;
(iv) kidney pathological ﬁndings such as ﬁbrosis and atrophy;
